-- China Life, Ping An Rally as Mirae Says Insurers to Gain on Higher Rates
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-10-20T03:07:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-20/china-life-ping-an-rally-as-mirae-says-insurers-to-gain-on-higher-rates.html
China Life Insurance Co. and Ping An
Insurance (Group) Co., the nation’s biggest life insurers, rose
more than 2 percent in Shanghai after Mirae Asset said life
insurers will outperform in a rising interest-rate environment.  China Life gained 2.6 percent to 27.35 yuan at 11:04 a.m.
local time, the highest since April 21. Ping An surged 3.8
percent to 65.01 yuan. China’s life insurers will benefit from
improved investment returns and gain flexibility to price
products, Ivan Leung, a Hong Kong-based analyst, wrote in a
report dated today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Allen Wan at 
 awan3@bloomberg.net  